<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,468,151,211]" box="[151,413,186,211]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,160,186,211]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">(</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[160,259,186,210]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Plate 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,404,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 25–32</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,258,966]" box="[151,1293,258,283]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,259,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 11.00 mm. (estimated, approximate ¼ of apex of forewings missing); female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,258,966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,464,295,319]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Large, robust species. General color black except for flavous crown and clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[159,232,330,354]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Plate1</figureCitation>
ID). Head large, nearly as wide as pronotum, anterior margin rounded; crown broad, about as wide as transocular width, slightly produce distally, lateral margins convergent basally, disk slightly depressed; eyes large, bulbous, occupying about 2/3 of entire dorsal area of head; pronotum moderately large, median length slightly less than median length of crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, median length about twice median length of pronotum; forewings long, broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed, clypeus long, lateral margins convex, with very faint median longitudinal carina; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow in basal half, expanded in apical half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,258,966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,375,582,607]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with distal half broad, caudal margin broadly rounded with small lobe and tuft of short setae (
<figureCitation box="[412,497,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long and broad, setaceous in distal half (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1305,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); style very long, nearly twice as long as aedeagus, robust with 2 short, subapical spines (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1150,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 27, 28</figureCitation>
); aedeagus short, tubular, sinuate in lateral view, apical ¼ narrowed, curved laterally, 4 short, curved setae subapically, gonopore near middle of shaft (
<figureCitation box="[251,388,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 29, 30</figureCitation>
); connective robust, T-shaped, stem long (
<figureCitation box="[861,944,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1412,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
